{
  "cells": [
    {
      "kind": 1,
      "value": "prec=100;",
      "languageId": "markdown"
    },
    {
      "kind": 1,
      "value": "\\<\\\nGenerate the matrix directly without resorting to taking a sum and \\\nderivatives of that sum\\\n\\>",
      "languageId": "markdown"
    },
    {
      "kind": 2,
      "value": "DirectMat[L_]:=\nModule[{k,n,l,tempMat},\ntempMat=ConstantArray[0,{L,L}];\nDo[tempMat[[Mod[n,L,1],Mod[n+k,L,1]]]=tempMat[[Mod[n,L,1],Mod[n+k,L,1]]]+(1)/(2)(-Sin[(\\[Pi])/(L)])/(Cos[(\\[Pi])/(L)]-Cos[(2 k \\[Pi])/(L)])/( L);\ntempMat[[Mod[n+k,L,1],Mod[n,L,1]]]=tempMat[[Mod[n+k,L,1],Mod[n,L,1]]]+(1)/(2)(-Sin[(\\[Pi])/(L)])/(Cos[(\\[Pi])/(L)]-Cos[(2 k \\[Pi])/(L)])/(L);\n,{k,1,L},{n,1,L}];\nReturn[tempMat,Module];\n]",
      "languageId": "wolfram"
    },
    {
      "kind": 1,
      "value": "\\<\\\nNumerical version with precision Nprec, to avoid storing analytic expressions \\\nof sines and cosines\\\n\\>",
      "languageId": "markdown"
    },
    {
      "kind": 2,
      "value": "DirectMatN[L_,NPrec_]:=\nModule[{k,n,l,tempMat},\ntempMat=ConstantArray[0,{L,L}];\nDo[tempMat[[Mod[n,L,1],Mod[n+k,L,1]]]=tempMat[[Mod[n,L,1],Mod[n+k,L,1]]]+N[(1)/(2)(-Sin[(\\[Pi])/(L)])/(Cos[(\\[Pi])/(L)]-Cos[(2 k \\[Pi])/(L)])/( L),NPrec];\ntempMat[[Mod[n+k,L,1],Mod[n,L,1]]]=tempMat[[Mod[n+k,L,1],Mod[n,L,1]]]+N[(1)/(2)(-Sin[(\\[Pi])/(L)])/(Cos[(\\[Pi])/(L)]-Cos[(2 k \\[Pi])/(L)])/(L),NPrec];\n,{k,1,L},{n,1,L}];\nReturn[tempMat,Module];\n]\nDirectMatNFast[L_,prec_]:=Module[{kernel},kernel=N[Table[-Sin[Pi/L]/(L (Cos[Pi/L]-Cos[2 Pi d/L])),{d,0,L-1}],prec];\nTable[kernel[[1+Mod[j-i,L]]],{i,1,L},{j,1,L}]]",
      "languageId": "wolfram"
    },
    {
      "kind": 1,
      "value": "Taking the traced matrix directly using a pre-calculated LxL matrix, and \nadding up the four identified locations under the trace. i.e. one should firstBold run DirectMat[L] or DirectMatN[L,NPrec] and store the result under some \nname, then Boldrun DirectTracedMat[L, l1, l2, [OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]matrix name\n[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote]]",
      "languageId": "markdown"
    },
    {
      "kind": 2,
      "value": "DirectTracedMat[L_,l1_,l2_,Mat_]:=\nModule[{k,l,i,j,tempMat,tempTracedMat,segments,segmentMaps},\ntempTracedMat=Mat[[1;;L/2,1;;L/2]];\nsegments={{1,l1},{l1+1,l1+l2},{l1+l2+1,L/2}};\nsegmentMaps={(L/2+l1+1-#1)&,(L/2+2l1+l2+1-#1)&,(Mod[L+l1+l2+1-#1,L,1])&};\nDo[\n(*go over the 9 blocks of the traced matrix, labeled by i j*)\nDo[\n(*go over all the entries in the i j block*)\ntempTracedMat[[k,l]]=tempTracedMat[[k,l]]+(Mat[[segmentMaps[[i]][k],l]]+Mat[[segmentMaps[[i]][k],segmentMaps[[j]][l]]]+Mat[[k,segmentMaps[[j]][l]]]);\n(*Print[{{k,l},{segmentMaps[[i]][k],l},{segmentMaps[[i]][k],segmentMaps[[j]][l]},{k,segmentMaps[[j]][l]}}];*)\n,{k,segments[[i,1]],segments[[i,2]]},{l,segments[[j,1]],segments[[j,2]]}];\n,{i,1,3},{j,1,3}];\nReturn[tempTracedMat,Module];\n]",
      "languageId": "wolfram"
    },
    {
      "kind": 1,
      "value": "\\<\\\nIf a matrix isn\\[CloseCurlyQuote]t given, the function generates it and feeds \\\nit into the above method\\\n\\>",
      "languageId": "markdown"
    },
    {
      "kind": 2,
      "value": "DirectTracedMat[L_,l1_,l2_]:=\nDirectTracedMat[L,l1,l2,DirectMat[L]]",
      "languageId": "wolfram"
    },
    {
      "kind": 1,
      "value": "Same algorithm but using the numerical LxL matrix",
      "languageId": "markdown"
    },
    {
      "kind": 2,
      "value": "DirectTracedMatN[L_,l1_,l2_,NPrec_]:=\nDirectTracedMat[L,l1,l2,DirectMatNFast[L,NPrec]]",
      "languageId": "wolfram"
    },
    {
      "kind": 1,
      "value": "\\<\\\nTaking the det after deleting the last row and column, (and numerical \\\nversion, and version with pre-calculated LxL matrix)\\\n\\>",
      "languageId": "markdown"
    },
    {
      "kind": 2,
      "value": "DirectDetPrime[L_,l1_,l2_]:=Times @@ DeleteCases[N[DirectTracedMat[L,l1,l2],prec]//Eigenvalues//Chop,0]\nDirectDetPrimeN[L_,l1_,l2_,Nprec_]:=Times @@ DeleteCases[DirectTracedMatN[L,l1,l2,prec]//Eigenvalues//Chop,0]",
      "languageId": "wolfram"
    },
    {
      "kind": 1,
      "value": "Taking the reduced traced matrix directly by starting with the a \npre-calculated full LxL matrix above, first calculating the (L/2)th row and \ncolumn, and adding up the four identified locations under the trace as well \nas the appropriate term from the (L/2)th row and column for the reduced \ntraced matrix. i.e. one should firstBold run DirectMatN[L, NPrec] or DirectMat[L] and store the result under some \nname, then Boldrun DirectTracedMat[L, l1, l2, [OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]matrix name\n[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote]]",
      "languageId": "markdown"
    },
    {
      "kind": 2,
      "value": "DirectRedTracedMat[L_,l1_,l2_,Mat_]:=\nModule[{k,l,i,j,tempMat,tempTracedMat,segments,segmentMaps, segmentFlag},\ntempMat=Mat;\ntempTracedMat=tempMat[[1;;L/2,1;;L/2]];\nsegmentFlag =\nIf[l1+l2==L/2,\n(*L/2 is actually in the second segment in this case*)\nsegments={{1,l1},{l1+1,l1+l2-1},{l1+l2+1,L/2}}; (*NOTE second segment ends early and third segment is now empty*)\nsegmentMaps={(L/2+l1+1-#1)&,(L/2+2l1+l2+1-#1)&,(Mod[L+l1+l2+1-#1,L,1])&};\n2,\nsegments={{1,l1},{l1+1,l1+l2},{l1+l2+1,L/2-1}}; (*NOTE this segment now ends at L/2-1 because we do L/2 separately*)\nsegmentMaps={(L/2+l1+1-#1)&,(L/2+2l1+l2+1-#1)&,(Mod[L+l1+l2+1-#1,L,1])&};\n3\n];\nDo[\n(*The L/2th row*)\nDo[\ntempTracedMat[[k,L/2]]=tempTracedMat[[k,L/2]]+(tempMat[[segmentMaps[[i]][k],L/2]]+tempMat[[segmentMaps[[i]][k],segmentMaps[[segmentFlag]][L/2]]]+tempMat[[k,segmentMaps[[segmentFlag]][L/2]]]);\n,{k,segments[[i,1]],segments[[i,2]]}];\n,{i,1,segmentFlag}\n];\n\nDo[\n(*The L/2th column*)\nDo[\ntempTracedMat[[L/2,l]]=tempTracedMat[[L/2,l]]+(tempMat[[segmentMaps[[segmentFlag]][L/2],l]]+tempMat[[segmentMaps[[segmentFlag]][L/2],segmentMaps[[j]][l]]]+tempMat[[L/2,segmentMaps[[j]][l]]]);\n,{l,segments[[j,1]],segments[[j,2]]}];\n,{j,1,segmentFlag}\n];\n\n(*the L/2, L/2 corner*)\ntempTracedMat[[L/2,L/2]]=tempTracedMat[[L/2,L/2]]+(tempMat[[segmentMaps[[segmentFlag]][L/2],L/2]]+tempMat[[segmentMaps[[segmentFlag]][L/2],segmentMaps[[segmentFlag]][L/2]]]+tempMat[[L/2,segmentMaps[[segmentFlag]][L/2]]]);\n\nDo[\n(*go over the 9 (or 4) blocks of the traced matrix, labeled by i j, now going up to L/2-1*)\nDo[\n(*go over all the entries in the i j block*)\n(*add the extra terms from the (L/2)th row and column*)\ntempTracedMat[[k,l]]=tempTracedMat[[k,l]]+(tempMat[[segmentMaps[[i]][k],l]]+tempMat[[segmentMaps[[i]][k],segmentMaps[[j]][l]]]+tempMat[[k,segmentMaps[[j]][l]]])+(-tempTracedMat[[k,L/2]]-tempTracedMat[[L/2,l]]+tempTracedMat[[L/2,L/2]]);\n(*Print[{{k,l},{segmentMaps[[i]][k],l},{segmentMaps[[i]][k],segmentMaps[[j]][l]},{k,segmentMaps[[j]][l]}}];*)\n,{k,segments[[i,1]],segments[[i,2]]},{l,segments[[j,1]],segments[[j,2]]}];\n,{i,1,segmentFlag},{j,1,segmentFlag}];\nReturn[tempTracedMat[[1;;-2 , 1;;-2]],Module];\n]",
      "languageId": "wolfram"
    },
    {
      "kind": 1,
      "value": "If no matrix given, generate it inside the method",
      "languageId": "markdown"
    },
    {
      "kind": 2,
      "value": "DirectRedTracedMat[L_,l1_,l2_]:=DirectRedTracedMat[L,l1,l2,DirectMat[L]]",
      "languageId": "wolfram"
    },
    {
      "kind": 1,
      "value": "Same algorithm but using the numerical LxL matrix",
      "languageId": "markdown"
    },
    {
      "kind": 2,
      "value": "DirectRedTracedMatN[L_,l1_,l2_,NPrec_]:=DirectRedTracedMat[L,l1,l2,DirectMatNFast[L,NPrec]]",
      "languageId": "wolfram"
    },
    {
      "kind": 1,
      "value": "Reduced determinants",
      "languageId": "markdown"
    },
    {
      "kind": 2,
      "value": "DirectRedDet[L_,l1_,l2_]:=Det[N[DirectRedTracedMat[L,l1,l2],prec]]/(L/2)\nDirectRedDetN[L_,l1_,l2_,NPrec_]:=Det[DirectRedTracedMatN[L,l1,l2,NPrec]]/(L/2)\nlogDetCholesky[m_?MatrixQ]:=Module[{r},r=CholeskyDecomposition[m];2 Total[Log[Diagonal[r]]]]",
      "languageId": "wolfram"
    },
    {
      "kind": 1,
      "value": "\\<\\\nCan generate the B matrix or B B^\\\\dagger matrix with roughly the same speed. \\\nThen can take either Abs[Det[B]]^2 or Exp[logDetCholesky[BB^\\\\dagger]]. Make \\\nsure to use Developer`ToPackedArray[...,Complex]\\\n\\>",
      "languageId": "markdown"
    },
    {
      "kind": 2,
      "value": "BmatFast[L_,l1_,l2_,NPrec_ : prec]:=Module[{k1,k2,k3,kernel,prime,matrix},\nprime=Join[Table[(L/2+l1+1-k1),{k1,1,l1}],Table[(L/2+2l1+l2+1-k2),{k2,l1+1,l1+l2}],Table[(L+l1+l2+1-k3),{k3,l1+l2+1,L/2}]];\nkernel=Table[N[E^(2Pi I n/L),NPrec],{n,0,L-1}];\nmatrix=Table[\nkernel[[Mod[m*k-k,L]+1]]-kernel[[Mod[m*prime[[k]]-k,L]+1]]\n,{k,1,L/2}\n,{m,1,L/2}];\nReturn[matrix,Module];\n];\nBdetFast[L_,l1_,l2_]:=Det[Developer`ToPackedArray[BmatFast[L,l1,l2],Complex]];",
      "languageId": "wolfram"
    },
    {
      "kind": 2,
      "value": "BBdaggermat[L_,l1_,l2_,Nprec_:prec]:=Module[{kernel,matrix,prime,k1,k2,k3},\nkernel = Join[Table[N[Exp[I*(L/4+1/2)*2*Pi*n/L]((Sin[Pi*n/2])/(Sin[Pi*n/L])),Nprec],{n,-L+1,-1}],{L/2},Table[N[Exp[I*(L/4+1/2)*2*Pi*n/L]((Sin[Pi*n/2])/(Sin[Pi*n/L])),Nprec],{n,1,L-1}]];\nprime=Join[Table[(L/2+l1+1-k1),{k1,1,l1}],Table[(L/2+2l1+l2+1-k2),{k2,l1+1,l1+l2}],Table[(L+l1+l2+1-k3),{k3,l1+l2+1,L/2}]];\nmatrix=Table[\nkernel[[k-l+L]]+kernel[[prime[[k]]-prime[[l]]+L]]-kernel[[k-prime[[l]]+L]]-kernel[[prime[[k]]-l+L]]\n,{k,1,L/2}\n,{l,1,L/2}];\nReturn[matrix,Module];\n]",
      "languageId": "wolfram"
    },
    {
      "kind": 1,
      "value": "Can also do the same for B^(n) matrix",
      "languageId": "markdown"
    },
    {
      "kind": 2,
      "value": "BnmatFast[L_,l1_,l2_,n_,NPrec_ : prec]:=Module[{k1,k2,k3,kernel,prime,matrix,mList,m},\nprime=Join[Table[(L/2+l1+1-k1),{k1,1,l1}],Table[(L/2+2l1+l2+1-k2),{k2,l1+1,l1+l2}],Table[(L+l1+l2+1-k3),{k3,l1+l2+1,L/2}]];\nkernel=Table[N[E^(2Pi I m/L),NPrec],{m,0,L-1}];\nmList=Join[{n},Range[2,L/2]];\nmatrix=Table[\nkernel[[Mod[m*k-k,L]+1]]-kernel[[Mod[m*prime[[k]]-k,L]+1]]\n,{k,1,L/2}\n,{m,mList}];\nReturn[matrix,Module];\n];\nBndetFast[L_,l1_,l2_,n_]:=Det[Developer`ToPackedArray[BnmatFast[L,l1,l2,n],Complex]];",
      "languageId": "wolfram"
    },
    {
      "kind": 1,
      "value": "### Generalized one-face B matrix from full boundary word\n\nFor a generic one-face ribbon graph, the traced disc boundary is encoded by a cyclic boundary word in which each edge label appears exactly twice. The generalized helper below takes that full boundary word, together with edge lengths, and constructs the site-by-site `prime` map by pairing the first and second occurrence of each edge with opposite local orientation.\n\nFor genus 2, the boundary word has length `18` and the edge-length list has length `9`. A convenience wrapper also allows the last edge length to be inferred from `L/2-Total[first 8]`.",
      "languageId": "markdown"
    },
    {
      "kind": 2,
      "value": "CompleteEdgeLengthsFromPartial[L_,edgeLens_List]:=Module[{half=Quotient[L,2],lens=edgeLens,lastLen},\nIf[OddQ[L],Return[$Failed,Module]];\nIf[Length[lens]==8,\nlastLen=half-Total[lens];\nIf[lastLen<=0,Return[$Failed,Module]];\nlens=Join[lens,{lastLen}]\n];\nIf[Total[lens]=!=half,Return[$Failed,Module]];\nIf[!And@@(IntegerQ/@lens),Return[$Failed,Module]];\nIf[!And@@Thread[lens>0],Return[$Failed,Module]];\nReturn[lens,Module]\n];\n\nPrimeDataFromBoundaryWord[L_,boundaryWord_List,edgeLens_List]:=Module[\n{lens,nEdges,segmentLens,starts,firstPos,secondPos,repSegs,repSites,prime},\nlens=CompleteEdgeLengthsFromPartial[L,edgeLens];\nIf[lens===$Failed,Return[$Failed,Module]];\nnEdges=Length[lens];\nIf[Length[boundaryWord]=!=2 nEdges,Return[$Failed,Module]];\nIf[Sort[boundaryWord]=!=Sort@Join[Range[nEdges],Range[nEdges]],Return[$Failed,Module]];\nsegmentLens=lens[[boundaryWord]];\nIf[Total[segmentLens]=!=L,Return[$Failed,Module]];\nstarts=Most[FoldList[Plus,1,segmentLens]];\nfirstPos=Association[];\nsecondPos=Association[];\nDo[\nIf[KeyExistsQ[firstPos,boundaryWord[[j]]],secondPos[boundaryWord[[j]]]=j,firstPos[boundaryWord[[j]]]=j]\n,{j,1,2 nEdges}];\nIf[Sort[Keys[firstPos]]=!=Range[nEdges]||Sort[Keys[secondPos]]=!=Range[nEdges],Return[$Failed,Module]];\nrepSegs=SortBy[Range[nEdges],firstPos[#]&];\nrepSites=Flatten@Table[Range[starts[[firstPos[e]]],starts[[firstPos[e]]]+lens[[e]]-1],{e,repSegs}];\nIf[Length[repSites]=!=Quotient[L,2],Return[$Failed,Module]];\nprime=Flatten@Table[Range[starts[[secondPos[e]]]+lens[[e]]-1,starts[[secondPos[e]]],-1],{e,repSegs}];\nIf[Length[prime]=!=Quotient[L,2],Return[$Failed,Module]];\n<|\"EdgeLengths\"->lens,\"SegmentLengths\"->segmentLens,\"SegmentStarts\"->starts,\"RepresentativeEdges\"->repSegs,\"RepresentativeSites\"->repSites,\"Prime\"->prime|>\n];\n\nBmatFastGeneralF1[L_,boundaryWord_List,edgeLens_List,NPrec_:prec]:=Module[{kernel,primeData,repSites,prime,matrix},\nprimeData=PrimeDataFromBoundaryWord[L,boundaryWord,edgeLens];\nIf[primeData===$Failed,Return[$Failed,Module]];\nrepSites=primeData[\"RepresentativeSites\"];\nprime=primeData[\"Prime\"];\nkernel=Table[N[E^(2Pi I n/L),NPrec],{n,0,L-1}];\nmatrix=Table[\nkernel[[Mod[m*repSites[[k]]-repSites[[k]],L]+1]]-kernel[[Mod[m*prime[[k]]-repSites[[k]],L]+1]]\n,{k,1,Length[repSites]}\n,{m,1,Length[repSites]}];\nReturn[matrix,Module]\n];\n\nBdetFastGeneralF1[L_,boundaryWord_List,edgeLens_List,NPrec_:prec]:=\nDet[Developer`ToPackedArray[BmatFastGeneralF1[L,boundaryWord,edgeLens,NPrec],Complex]];\n\nBmatFastGenus2[L_,boundaryWord_List,l1_,l2_,l3_,l4_,l5_,l6_,l7_,l8_,NPrec_:prec]:=\nBmatFastGeneralF1[L,boundaryWord,{l1,l2,l3,l4,l5,l6,l7,l8},NPrec];\n\nBdetFastGenus2[L_,boundaryWord_List,l1_,l2_,l3_,l4_,l5_,l6_,l7_,l8_,NPrec_:prec]:=\nDet[Developer`ToPackedArray[BmatFastGenus2[L,boundaryWord,l1,l2,l3,l4,l5,l6,l7,l8,NPrec],Complex]];\n\nThetaBoundaryWord={1,2,3,1,2,3};",
      "languageId": "wolfram"
    },
    {
      "kind": 1,
      "value": "Example: the genus-1 theta graph is represented by the boundary word `ThetaBoundaryWord={1,2,3,1,2,3}`. The generalized helper recovers the old `BmatFast` when the edge lengths are `{l1,l2,L/2-l1-l2}`.",
      "languageId": "markdown"
    },
    {
      "kind": 2,
      "value": "BmatFastThetaFromGeneral[L_,l1_,l2_,NPrec_:prec]:=\nBmatFastGeneralF1[L,ThetaBoundaryWord,{l1,l2},NPrec]",
      "languageId": "wolfram"
    },
    {
      "kind": 1,
      "value": "Stored genus-2 one-face boundary words from the Python topology data:",
      "languageId": "markdown"
    },
    {
      "kind": 1,
      "value": "### Testing",
      "languageId": "markdown"
    },
